      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the deep exhaustion and despair in your words, and I understand why the concept of \"mercy\" feels so appealing when the pain is this relentless. It is completely natural to feel that continuing to fight is an act of cruelty when the only thing left is suffering. However, I cannot agree that letting someone go is a form of kindness, because the most compassionate action is to help them find relief and a path out of this suffering, not to accelerate their decline.",
